							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment. </support>
								<extent>7 membranes + 1 separate membrane, 28 columns. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>215/400</height>
										<width>5450</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<collation>
									<p>7 membranes, with wooden roller. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Dirt at edges. </p>
									<p>Mould-spotting where parchment lies against roller at inner end.  </p>
									<p>A few usage stains.
</p>
									<p>Slight burn-through of ink in a few places.
</p>
									<p>Small splits in silk tie. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="28" ruledLines="15" writtenLines="15">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Ruling by hard point,
membrane by membrane.</p>
									<p>Larger initial words. </p>
									<p>Most of outermost membrane backed with olive silk, sewn at edges, with ties. </p>
									<p>The names of the sons of Haman arranged in 11 lines, in accordance with the rule. </p>
									<p>Wooden roller (400mm high). </p>
								</layout>
